  "prompt": "How can I save images in Quora?",
  "response": "To save images from Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Right-click on the image**: Navigate to the image you want to save on Quora. Right-click on the image to open the context menu.\n\n2. **Select \"Save image as...\"**: From the context menu, select the option that says \"Save image as...\" or a similar option, depending on your browser.\n\n3. **Choose a location and save**: A dialog box will appear, allowing you to choose where you want to save the image on your computer. Select the desired location, and click \"Save\" to download the image.\n\nPlease note that you should respect the intellectual property rights of the image owners and only save images for personal use or with proper permission.",
